article.headline: E. Kentucky 63, Jacksonville St. 51
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. (AP) -- Adam Leonard scored 20 points as Eastern Kentucky rallied for a 63-51 win over Jacksonville State on Thursday night. Leonard scored 14 points in the second half to help the Colonels (17-9, 12-6) recover from a 12-point deficit and extend their winning streak to seven games with three remaining. The Colonels sealed the win by connecting on 7-of-8 free throws in the final 1:30. Darnell Dials rounded out two Eastern players in double figures with 12 points. Eastern never led until Julian Mascoll connected on a 3-pointer with 16:43 left to give the Colonels a 32-31 advantage. Mascoll's trey was part of a 13-0 run that turned a 31-27 deficit into a 40-31 lead. Jacksonville tied the score twice in the final 11 minutes, but failed to regain the lead. The Gamecocks (8-19, 6-12) connected on five 3-pointers in the first half, including three in a 15-2 run that turned a 9-9 tie into a 23-11 lead with 10:44 left in the first half. Will Ginn hit three of Jacksonville's shots from long range in the opening half. Eastern scored 16 of the last 21 points of the half, narrowing the deficit to 28-27. Courtney Bradley led Jacksonville with 16 points, followed by Nick Smith with 14 and Erik Adams with 10.
